2006: an earthquake of magnitude 6.8 struck the southern area of Java, the most populous island of Indonesia, causing a tsunami that broke out against the southern coast killing almost 700 people.
2009: an earthquake of magnitude 7.6 fell near the city of Padang, capital of the province of West Sumatra.
