2010: a 7.5 magnitude earthquake struck one of the Mentawai islands off Sumatra, causing a tsunami of 10 metres that destroyed dozens of villages and killed about 300 people.
2016: a slight earthquake struck the Pidie Jaya Regency in Aceh causing destruction and panic in people who remembered the devastation of the 2004 earthquake and tsunami.
